5. Implemented Backend Features

 5.1 User Registration

Users can register by providing an ID, username, and password.

API:

POST /api/signup

The system checks that the ID and username are unique.

 5.2 Login System

Users can log in with their username and password.

API:


POST /api/login

The system checks whether the username exists and whether the password is correct.

5.3 Password Validation

The password validation system checks that the password includes:

 Uppercase letter
 Lowercase letter
 Number
 Special character
 At least eight characters

The password must not contain the username.

5.4 Temporary Account Lock

The system temporarily locks a user account after several incorrect login attempts.

5.5 Admin CLI

The Admin CLI was implemented for managing users, groups, and reported messages.

Available options:
text
1. Add User
2. List Users
3. Remove User
4. Add Group
5. List Groups
6. Remove Group
7. Add User To Group
8. Remove User From Group
9. Show Group Members
10. Show Reported Messages
0. Exit

 5.6 Group Management

The administrator can:

Create groups
 Delete groups
 Add users to groups
 Remove users from groups
 View group members

5.7 Messaging System

Users can send messages to a group chat.

API:

POST /api/messages

Messages can be retrieved by using a chat ID.

GET /api/messages?chatId=g1


5.8 Reported Messages

A message can be reported through the API.


POST /api/messages/report

Reported messages can be viewed through option `10` in the Admin CLI.

